        /*
        	UPDATED - BRENTON KELLY - 9.16.2016 - Case: 00373150
            Intended Functionality:
            - Homepage banner images is toggled on/off via the template options that you pointed out to me. 
			- Channel banner images are toggled on/off simply by the presence of an image in template configuration. If there is no image then no banner should show. The template options check box should not affect this. 
			- The banner under "Template Options" under settings was a banner for the HomePage only — and it was something that we only occasionally choose to use. 
			- The banners under "Channel Banners" would only be active on designated channels if we mapped an image to them, and associated that image to the Channel Name. 
			- If no image was mapped and associated with a channel, then no banner would appear.
        */
